race.comment: WANJINA ROSE (6) raced wide without cover at the tail of the field then stoked up late to grab third in an eye-catching performance over 1200m at Port Macquarie. Drops 1kg after the claim in an easier race. Looks the one to beat with the help of a perfect draw. ENDANGERED SPECIES (7) backs up seven days after a moderate midfield finish in a similar race to this at Inverell. Was beaten under a length at this track in a stronger race earlier this prep. Worth another chance with the blinkers going on. VIADELAMORE (1) has been going around in middle distance contests for some time with limited success. Back in class today and might be a surprise packet. Giving IN THE FINE PRINT (4) another chance off a 44-day let-up. Finished fourth in a BM58 here off a similar break back in August - in the mix on that form. SASKATOON BERRY (9) is next best - scratched from an earlier race to be kept for this.
